Using gdown package (small and quick)

# Update and upgrade existing packages


pkg update && pkg upgrade -y

# Install Python and necessary tools


pkg install python -y
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install gdown



# Navigate to the folder where you want the downloads


# Download a folder (use -c to resume if interrupted)


gdown -c --folder "https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/YOUR_FOLDER_ID_HERE"





Using rclone package (complex for setting up)

# Install rclone
pkg install rclone -y

# Start the configuration process
rclone config

Configuration Steps:
Type n for a new remote.
Name it gdrive.
Select the number corresponding to drive (Google Drive).
Leave Client ID and Secret blank (press Enter).
Select scope 1 (Full access).
Type n for advanced config and n for auto-config.
Paste the authorization URL into your mobile browser, copy the code provided by Google, and paste it back into Termux

# Check size of a specific folder

rclone size gdrive:"Your Folder Name" -P

# Copy only PDFs from a remote folder to your phone

rclone copy gdrive:"Main_Folder" /sdcard/Documents/PDFs --include "*.pdf" --include "*/" -P

Write the name of folder in place of Main_folder


